SimpleCronScheduler

This is a simple scheduler that can run one job after another. Jobs are executed in a FIFO order.

To install the scheduler make the file scheduler_install.sh executeable (chmod +x) and then run it.

To add a job to the scheduler type scheduler add [jobname] into your shell. The jobname refers to a
script that needs to be placed at /var/scheduler/scripts. After executing a script all ouput wil be
saved at /var/scheduler/output and send via email (using mail command) to the email address entered
during insallation.
